(Keyword - people were dying from blood transfusions,  if you mix blood from two people with different blood types the blood can clump which may be dangerous leading to death, donor blood,  it’s important for the donor and the recipient to have blood types, People with blood group A can safely get group A blood  and people with blood group B can receive group B blood)

(Keyword - Type O negative red blood cells,  O negative blood cells don't have antibodies to A, B or Rh antigens called “universal” red cell donors as they can donate blood to anyone with any blood type)
